item.description:
There is a zen saying: &ldquo;ordinary mind is Buddha mind&rdquo;. I did understand this saying, but yesterday I realised it in a whole new way: Often what prompts us to start investigating &rsquo;this spiritual stuff&rsquo;, is a feeling of isolation; we feel as if, as this quote from A.E. Housman illustrates —
&lsquo;I, a stranger and afraid, in a world I never made.&rsquo;
We feel cut off from the source of life in some undefinable way, atomised by societal conditioning and our own past.
